<i>Written and Directed by
WONG KAR-WAI</i>

12
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:21,475
Hello.

13
00:02:21,558 --> 00:02:24,019
<i>Hello, is this Ha-tau? This is Auntie.</i>

14
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:27,481
<i>You still asleep? I'll call you later.</i>

15
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:29,066
Okay.

16
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,253
<i>It's Auntie again.</i>

17
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:53,382
<i>You're still not up?
All right. I'll call you later.</i>

18
00:02:53,465 --> 00:02:57,177
No, it's okay.
Go ahead.

19
00:02:57,260 --> 00:03:02,307
<i>Your young cousin isn't feeling well
and has to see a doctor.</i>

20
00:03:02,391 --> 00:03:04,142
<i>Instead of having her
travel back and forth,</i>

21
00:03:04,226 --> 00:03:06,436
<i>I'm sending her to stay with you
for a few days, okay?</i>

22
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:09,272
I have a younger cousin?

23
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:12,651
<i>She's your second uncle's daughter,
Ah-Ngor.</i>

24
00:03:22,411 --> 00:03:23,995
Who could that be?

25
00:03:36,383 --> 00:03:39,511
I thought you were out.
I'm Ah-Ngor.

26
00:03:40,095 --> 00:03:41,596
You're my cousin, right?

27
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,724
Come in. Make yourself at home.

28
00:03:43,807 --> 00:03:45,767
There's the kitchen and bathroom.

29
00:03:46,685 --> 00:03:49,938
Listen, if anyone calls,
tell them to call back later.

30
00:04:05,871 --> 00:04:07,622
<i>Hello. Can I speak to Brother Wah?</i>

31
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,375
He's sleeping. Who's calling?

32
00:04:10,459 --> 00:04:13,336
<i>Ha! You don't even know me,
so you must be new.</i>

33
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:14,963
<i>I'm Fly. Who are you?</i>

34
00:04:15,046 --> 00:04:16,256
I'm his cousin.

35
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:18,717
<i>Cousin? Never mind.</i>

36
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,428
<i>Tell him I'm waiting
to do business with Fat Carl.</i>

37
00:04:21,511 --> 00:04:23,638
<i>- Have him call me when he gets up.</i>
- Okay.

38
00:05:27,494 --> 00:05:29,663
<i>Hello, cousin. Isn't Brother Wah up yet?</i>

39
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:34,417
Not yet. Is it urgent?
Want me to wake him up?

40
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:36,670
<i>No. When he gets up,</i>

41
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:39,256
<i>tell him I'm still waiting for Fat Carl.
Have him call me.</i>

42
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:40,799
Okay.

43
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:34,120
Go sleep in the bedroom if you're tired.

44
00:06:34,144 --> 00:06:35,664
I'll sleep in the living room tonight.

45
00:06:43,612 --> 00:06:45,363
Why do you wear that mask?

46
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:46,865
So I don't infect other people.

47
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:51,573
What kind of disease is it?

48
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:53,830
The doctor said
my lungs are malfunctioning

49
00:06:53,914 --> 00:06:55,373
and told me to see a specialist.

50
00:06:57,542 --> 00:07:00,003
Don't worry. You're not gonna die.

51
00:07:02,797 --> 00:07:04,591
Just eat more oranges and you'll be fine.

52
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:10,347
Tastes strange.

53
00:07:19,064 --> 00:07:23,068
A guy named Fly
called a couple times for you.

54
00:07:26,029 --> 00:07:27,614
Really? What did he say?

55
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:34,120
<i>Hello, little cousin. Is he up yet?</i>

56
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,081
Hello.

57
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,084
<i>I'm at Fat Carl's place,
collecting what he owes.</i>

58
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:41,044
You're kidding! What's taking you so long?

59
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:43,630
He's jerking you around.
Stay there. I'll be right over.

60
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:59,646
I can't have dinner with you tonight.
You'll have to go out on your own.

61
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:04,567
Here, get yourself something to eat.

62
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:06,152
The key's under the mat.

63
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:09,823
And take that thing off. It's ugly.

64
00:08:22,085 --> 00:08:23,837
Have a cup of tea first.

65
00:08:27,966 --> 00:08:30,969
Fat Carl, I'm telling you,

66
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:34,139
I'm doing you a favor
talking with you this long.

67
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:39,144
If I'm not well-known,
it's not 'cause I'm a weakling.

68
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:41,771
My big brother tells me
to keep a low profile.

69
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:43,815
You know Airplane?

70
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:47,444
He ran up $1,600 in debt
and was just two days late in paying.

71
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,988
Now he can't fly,
and he has to use a wheelchair.

72
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:52,991
I did that with my own two hands.

73
00:08:54,284 --> 00:08:56,119
You trying to scare me?

74
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:59,330
Airplane's a nobody!
You can't compare him to me!

75
00:08:59,414 --> 00:09:00,999
Let me tell you something!

76
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:03,918
Fat Carl doesn't pay debts!

77
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:07,589
You know that guy called Tubby?
He was a lot tougher than you.

78
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:09,257
Now they call him Skinny.

79
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:10,967
You know why?

80
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:12,927
He tried to collect too,

81
00:09:13,011 --> 00:09:14,596
and I beat him half to death.

82
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:16,431
He's only got one eye left now.

83
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:21,311
You been at this just two years
and you have the nerve to come to me?

84
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:24,731
I got more knife scars
than you have hairs on your legs!

85
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:28,234
Scars? My big brother's only got one,
so I'll cut myself if you have any!

86
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:30,612
Then start cutting!

87
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,615
Aren't you guys finished yet?

88
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:35,492
We're just getting started.

89
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:37,994
Just getting started after this long?

90
00:09:39,704 --> 00:09:40,955
Nobody move!

91
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:43,416
You gonna pay what you owe?

92
00:09:44,626 --> 00:09:46,669
Yeah!

93
00:09:46,753 --> 00:09:47,754
I never said I wouldn't!

94
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:52,342
I can't believe it was that easy.

95
00:09:53,051 --> 00:09:55,178
I could tell he was
a sheep in wolf's clothing.

96
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,847
If they had any guts,
they would have jumped you.

97
00:09:57,931 --> 00:09:58,932
You're right.

98
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:00,934
- Here.
- Thank you.

99
00:10:12,362 --> 00:10:13,738
Hey, Brother Wah.

100
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,658
Here to see Mabel?

101
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:19,702
- She's not here yet.
- I'll wait for her downstairs.

102
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:46,729
Mabel!

103
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,191
Come here.

104
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:54,237
I haven't eaten yet. Will you join me?

105
00:10:58,074 --> 00:10:59,659
It's okay if you don't want to.

106
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:07,208
- Why were you so late for work?
- I just got out of the hospital.

107
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:11,337
The hospital? Why?
Did they pump your stomach again?

108
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:13,256
I had an abortion!

109
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:19,679
Is this a joke?

110
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:21,431
Take it that way if you want.

111
00:11:25,143 --> 00:11:27,770
Why didn't you tell me you were pregnant?

112
00:11:28,271 --> 00:11:29,647
Did you ever give me a chance?

113
00:11:29,731 --> 00:11:31,858
Three days I waited, but you never called!

114
00:11:33,026 --> 00:11:35,737
You could have called me.

115
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:39,199
Call you? To say what?

116
00:11:39,282 --> 00:11:41,618
That you should marry me?
That I'm getting an abortion?

117
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:44,537
We were together six years,
and what did I get in the end?

118
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:48,458
You're still not mine,
and I'm not even better off for it.

119
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:51,544
I'm so poor I had to borrow
from my mother for the abortion.

120
00:11:51,628 --> 00:11:54,088
- And what for?
- Are you done?

121
00:11:57,759 --> 00:12:00,178
You knew what kind of guy I was
from the day we met!

122
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:05,433
Don't stay with me
if it's marriage and money you're after!

123
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:09,771
Don't think I'll feel sorry forever
'cause you got an abortion.

124
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:11,481
I won't.

125
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,441
You say that now, but I know you will!

126
00:12:14,984 --> 00:12:18,488
So you don't give a damn about me?
Fine!

127
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:19,989
I destroyed your baby!

128
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:23,284
And I'm gonna tell everyone
that I had your baby aborted,

129
00:12:23,368 --> 00:12:25,248
so you'll feel guilty
for the rest of your life!

130
00:12:30,375 --> 00:12:31,542
Congratulations.

131
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:33,628
You win!

132
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:15,003
Cousin.

133
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:19,590
Are you all right?

134
00:13:44,282 --> 00:13:45,408
Cousin.

135
00:13:48,369 --> 00:13:51,748
What's the matter, cousin?

136
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:55,043
Did you break up with someone?

137
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:01,674
What did you say?

138
00:14:06,137 --> 00:14:07,722
What did you say?

139
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:17,607
I'm warning you...

140
00:14:18,608 --> 00:14:20,443
never say those words again...

141
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:22,987
or I'll throw you out.

142
00:15:37,937 --> 00:15:39,480
Did you see the doctor?

143
00:15:39,981 --> 00:15:41,441
I just came back from the hospital.

144
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,153
What did he say?

145
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:47,363
I get the results tomorrow.

146
00:15:57,540 --> 00:16:00,251
Have you eaten yet?
Let's go get something.

147
00:16:02,003 --> 00:16:03,504
I cooked.

148
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:15,892
Fly called for you again this morning.

149
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:19,479
What did that rat say?

150
00:16:20,563 --> 00:16:23,441
Nothing special.
Just small talk.

151
00:16:25,026 --> 00:16:26,736
Didn't he ask anything about me?

152
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:28,446
Like what?

153
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:32,492
Like what happened last night.

154
00:16:36,913 --> 00:16:38,581
He just asked one question.

155
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:43,836
One question?
What was it?

156
00:16:44,921 --> 00:16:46,631
I'm afraid to tell you.

157
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:50,218
Just tell me what he said.

158
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,261
You sure?

159
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:56,265
He asked, if you broke up.

160
00:17:08,945 --> 00:17:12,406
You've been in all day.
Why don't you go out?

161
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:15,493
No place to go.

162
00:17:16,536 --> 00:17:18,287
I've got no friends in Kowloon.

163
00:17:23,251 --> 00:17:26,337
Finish up
and I'll take you out.

164
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:40,476
Are you in school, or do you work?

165
00:17:41,644 --> 00:17:43,521
I'm working already.

166
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:44,981
What kind of job?

167
00:17:45,523 --> 00:17:47,400
In a friend's restaurant.

168
00:17:48,818 --> 00:17:49,986
Is he your boyfriend?

169
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:55,283
Not really.

170
00:17:55,366 --> 00:17:57,034
Everybody calls him Uncle Tang.

171
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:03,499
Hey, let's go see a movie later.

172
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:06,502
If you're free.
Don't feel you have to keep me company.

173
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:35,990
Are you the backup?

174
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:40,161
Ah-Site, how much did you lose?

175
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:42,079
Five hundred.

176
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:47,501
I won't play for that little.

177
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:51,297
Let's settle this with one game...
for a grand.

178
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,507
You in?

179
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:55,426
A grand?

180
00:18:55,509 --> 00:18:57,470
What do you say, Snooker King?

181
00:18:57,553 --> 00:19:00,931
I should show you my stuff
for a grand?

182
00:19:01,015 --> 00:19:03,809
I'll play you one-handed for two grand.

183
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:05,686
One-handed?

184
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:07,813
You're on!

185
00:19:09,482 --> 00:19:10,733
Ah-Site.

186
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:14,654
Piece of cake.

187
00:19:30,127 --> 00:19:32,338
Another ball in the pocket.
How about that?

188
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:46,268
Snooker King is really great!

189
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:57,321
Ah-Site, how many points am I behind?

190
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:03,494
No need to count.
He's 30 points ahead.

191
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:06,122
He'll still be five ahead
even if you knock all the rest in.

192
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:07,581
What do you say?

193
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:10,626
This calls for a special cue.

194
00:20:12,545 --> 00:20:15,339
Ah-Site,
my special cue.

195
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:28,644
Come on.

196
00:20:30,396 --> 00:20:32,273
"This little piggie went to market"...

197
00:20:33,274 --> 00:20:34,859
Step aside.

198
00:20:35,443 --> 00:20:37,236
"This little piggie stayed home"...

199
00:20:38,738 --> 00:20:40,406
Give us some room.

200
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,200
"This little piggie had roast beef"...

201
00:20:44,577 --> 00:20:46,245
We need to set up this shot.

202
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:54,920
Too easy. Let's make it harder for him.

203
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:59,425
Watch out.
You just lost seven points.

204
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:00,634
Take your shot.

205
00:21:02,887 --> 00:21:05,014
Shoot!

206
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:07,391
You take me for a fool?

207
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:12,229
Watch out!

208
00:21:13,439 --> 00:21:14,648
- You okay?
- Run!

209
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:41,050
Come on, you idiot!

210
00:21:42,092 --> 00:21:43,928
Stop!

211
00:21:44,595 --> 00:21:45,805
Stop!

212
00:21:53,437 --> 00:21:55,397
Out of the way, damn it!

213
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,112
What the hell!

214
00:22:16,544 --> 00:22:17,962
Die!

215
00:22:33,519 --> 00:22:34,603
To hell with you!

216
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:53,539
Big Brother!

217
00:22:56,292 --> 00:22:57,668
Big Brother!

218
00:22:58,627 --> 00:22:59,837
Big Brother!

219
00:23:22,985 --> 00:23:24,445
Ready?

220
00:23:26,697 --> 00:23:27,698
Yeah.

221
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:54,183
Shut up!

222
00:27:09,753 --> 00:27:11,088
Are you all right?

223
00:27:11,922 --> 00:27:13,382
Yeah, I'm okay.

224
00:27:27,646 --> 00:27:29,481
Why don't you go to sleep? It's late.

225
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:14,651
<i>Cousin, the report said my health is fine.</i>

226
00:28:15,152 --> 00:28:17,446
<i>I wanted to stay and celebrate with you,</i>

227
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:20,574
<i>but Auntie said the weather's nice,
so the restaurant's busy.</i>

228
00:28:21,325 --> 00:28:23,285
<i>Uncle Tang wanted me to get back earlier.</i>

229
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:26,496
<i>I called your name twice,
but you didn't answer.</i>

230
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:28,457
<i>You must have been very tired.</i>

231
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:30,042
<i>Summer's coming,</i>

232
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:32,586
<i>and lots of people
will vacation on Lantau Island.</i>

233
00:28:32,669 --> 00:28:34,922
<i>Do you get vacations in your line of work?</i>

234
00:28:35,756 --> 00:28:37,841
<i>I made a meal for you in the kitchen.</i>

235
00:28:38,425 --> 00:28:40,469
<i>I also bought a few more glasses.</i>

236
00:28:41,094 --> 00:28:43,680
<i>I knew they'd all get broken
sooner or later,</i>

237
00:28:43,764 --> 00:28:45,224
<i>so I hid one of them.</i>

238
00:28:45,682 --> 00:28:47,726
<i>One day, when you need that glass,</i>

239
00:28:47,809 --> 00:28:51,230
<i>give me a call,
and I'll tell you where it's hidden.</i>

240
00:28:51,313 --> 00:28:52,898
<i>Bye-bye. Ah-Ngor</i>

241
00:29:30,477 --> 00:29:31,812
Hey, everybody!

242
00:29:34,273 --> 00:29:37,359
Turn that down!

243
00:29:44,866 --> 00:29:47,244
Honored relatives and guests,

244
00:29:47,327 --> 00:29:50,080
today is my brother Ah-Site's wedding day.

245
00:29:50,163 --> 00:29:53,166
We've prepared
some modest food to serve you.

246
00:29:53,250 --> 00:29:54,334
So drink up.

247
00:29:54,418 --> 00:29:55,711
To my brother!

248
00:29:59,506 --> 00:30:01,800
See, I told you $200 was too much!

249
00:30:01,883 --> 00:30:03,885
Who knew he was so cheap
he'd have it on the roof?

250
00:30:04,469 --> 00:30:05,971
Please help yourselves.

251
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:08,056
After you.

252
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:15,689
Stop acting like that. After you.

253
00:30:16,148 --> 00:30:17,190
Look this way.

254
00:30:18,734 --> 00:30:21,153
One more!

255
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:22,362
That's enough!

256
00:30:22,446 --> 00:30:26,033
Go get your in-laws
for a picture.

257
00:30:26,116 --> 00:30:28,160
Hurry up. Go!

258
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:36,918
- Father, will you join us for a picture?
- No.

259
00:30:37,002 --> 00:30:39,087
- Come on, Father.
- No.

260
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:44,468
Don't be like that.
Come have your picture taken.

261
00:30:44,551 --> 00:30:46,678
No. What's the point?

262
00:30:46,762 --> 00:30:48,221
This is a disgrace!

263
00:30:48,972 --> 00:30:52,267
Hurry up and finish
before I pass out from the heat.

264
00:30:52,351 --> 00:30:54,227
Don't be like that.

265
00:30:54,311 --> 00:30:56,980
You don't hold a reception
if you don't have the money.

266
00:30:57,064 --> 00:31:00,108
Unheard of,
having it on the roof!

267
00:31:05,906 --> 00:31:07,407
I just can't get through to you.

268
00:31:08,033 --> 00:31:10,577
Can't you ever do anything right?

269
00:31:11,203 --> 00:31:15,248
This is your brother's big day.
Why did you make it so shabby?

270
00:31:15,791 --> 00:31:18,502
Think I didn't want to do it up big?

271
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:20,629
But I've got no money. What could I do?

272
00:31:24,466 --> 00:31:25,842
He complains too much.

273
00:31:40,816 --> 00:31:41,983
Shithead.

274
00:31:43,402 --> 00:31:44,444
What did you say?

275
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:46,863
What did I say?

276
00:31:47,614 --> 00:31:49,157
I said you're a shithead!

277
00:31:49,241 --> 00:31:51,660
I served you shark's fin
and abalone, didn't I?

278
00:31:52,119 --> 00:31:54,389
So what if there's no air conditioning?
Why complain so much?

279
00:31:54,413 --> 00:31:57,999
If you ask me,
this good food is wasted on you!

280
00:31:58,583 --> 00:32:01,628
I only served abalone
'cause your son-in-law said you loved it.

281
00:32:01,711 --> 00:32:03,880
Had I known you were such a jerk,

282
00:32:03,964 --> 00:32:07,050
I'd have served you shit instead!

283
00:32:07,134 --> 00:32:09,928
You want to die?
Don't you dare throw things at me!

284
00:32:10,011 --> 00:32:11,805
Let me go! I'll kill him!

285
00:32:11,888 --> 00:32:14,683
- You wanna fight?
- Big Brother, don't!

286
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:16,560
Wanna fight, do you?

287
00:32:17,227 --> 00:32:19,813
What are you doing? Get out of here!

288
00:32:19,896 --> 00:32:22,816
And you keep quiet!

289
00:32:24,151 --> 00:32:25,569
Get lost!

290
00:32:25,652 --> 00:32:27,779
Sit down! Sit!

291
00:32:28,363 --> 00:32:31,908
Was I right or what?
A real shithead, isn't he?

292
00:32:31,992 --> 00:32:34,536
- You arguing with your big brother?
- Isn't he a bastard?

293
00:32:34,619 --> 00:32:36,997
Go on talking, I dare you!

294
00:32:41,543 --> 00:32:43,587
After all, he is Ah-Site's father-in-law.

295
00:32:44,337 --> 00:32:48,091
You're making things hard
for your little brother.

296
00:32:48,175 --> 00:32:52,220
All right, it's my fault.
I'm in the wrong.

297
00:32:58,727 --> 00:33:00,145
Younger brother...

298
00:33:02,606 --> 00:33:04,191
I've done you wrong.

299
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:07,819
Someday when I strike it rich...

300
00:33:10,238 --> 00:33:11,740
I'll throw you another banquet.

301
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:27,923
<i>I knew it was our turn,</i>

302
00:33:28,006 --> 00:33:29,758
<i>but it all happened so quickly.</i>

303
00:33:29,841 --> 00:33:31,968
<i>The cops arrested our guys last night.</i>

304
00:33:32,052 --> 00:33:34,596
If it had just been the small-fries,
then no big deal,

305
00:33:34,679 --> 00:33:36,556
but Big-Mouth Kay handles the money.

306
00:33:45,023 --> 00:33:48,443
They say the cops
are making a deal with him.

307
00:33:48,527 --> 00:33:51,404
They'll help him out if he squeals on us.

308
00:33:51,488 --> 00:33:54,449
It could be really serious.

309
00:33:54,533 --> 00:33:56,743
So Godfather sent me to tell you

310
00:33:56,826 --> 00:34:00,205
not to make any unnecessary trouble
these days.

311
00:34:03,083 --> 00:34:05,001
Hey, the police are outside.

312
00:34:05,085 --> 00:34:07,212
Any of you bastards got drugs and weapons,

313
00:34:07,295 --> 00:34:09,256
go take care of them, quick.

314
00:34:11,132 --> 00:34:13,343
Ah-Wah, you've got a visitor outside.

315
00:34:13,426 --> 00:34:14,553
Thanks.

316
00:34:20,642 --> 00:34:22,602
- What brings you here?
- I gotta talk to you.

317
00:34:23,144 --> 00:34:25,272
Your brother Fly owes us.

318
00:34:25,355 --> 00:34:28,733
He's missed a couple payments
and doesn't return our calls.

319
00:34:29,359 --> 00:34:31,528
My big brother sent me to tell you

320
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:35,282
if he doesn't pay by tomorrow,
he gets no more chances.

321
00:34:36,825 --> 00:34:40,245
Tell Tony I can take care of my own guys.

322
00:34:40,870 --> 00:34:43,123
I'll talk to Fly about the money.

323
00:34:43,206 --> 00:34:46,209
If this is true,
I'll bring him to see Tony tomorrow.

324
00:34:55,885 --> 00:34:58,179
Did you wanna see me?

325
00:35:03,893 --> 00:35:05,395
You been hard up for money recently?

326
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:10,650
I'm always hard up for money.

327
00:35:11,151 --> 00:35:16,281
But I'm used to it.
I've got big prospects.

328
00:35:17,157 --> 00:35:21,036
A fortune-teller told me
I'd strike it rich by 30.

329
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:22,871
Everything's gonna be great.

330
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:25,373
I'll be sitting pretty.

331
00:35:25,457 --> 00:35:27,083
Won't need to hang around here.

332
00:35:29,502 --> 00:35:32,797
Did this fortune-teller also mention
you won't make it to 30?

333
00:35:32,881 --> 00:35:34,466
No.

334
00:35:35,091 --> 00:35:38,053
I heard you borrowed money from Tony.

335
00:35:42,223 --> 00:35:43,767
What are you saying?

336
00:35:43,850 --> 00:35:45,435
That's English.

337
00:35:45,518 --> 00:35:47,646
You know I don't understand English,
so why speak it?

338
00:35:48,897 --> 00:35:52,484
I'll ask you again.
Did you borrow money from Tony?

339
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:53,943
No.

340
00:35:55,195 --> 00:35:57,656
Then why are they looking for you?

341
00:35:58,239 --> 00:36:00,241
They're eating around the corner.

342
00:36:00,325 --> 00:36:02,243
- Want me to have 'em come over?
- Fine.

343
00:36:09,459 --> 00:36:10,960
Who are you winking at?

344
00:36:12,379 --> 00:36:13,880
How much did you borrow?

345
00:36:14,964 --> 00:36:16,299
How much?

346
00:36:17,384 --> 00:36:19,552
Not much. Take it easy.

347
00:36:19,636 --> 00:36:21,262
"Not much" is still money.

348
00:36:21,346 --> 00:36:22,764
How much?

349
00:36:22,847 --> 00:36:26,393
Couple hundred bucks. No big deal.
Don't listen to them.

350
00:36:26,476 --> 00:36:28,770
They wouldn't come to me
for a couple hundred bucks.

351
00:36:31,231 --> 00:36:32,732
You gonna tell me?

352
00:36:37,737 --> 00:36:40,323
A wedding banquet
and a gift for the bride.

353
00:36:40,407 --> 00:36:41,825
You figure it out.

354
00:36:58,049 --> 00:36:59,551
There's 8,000.

355
00:37:02,721 --> 00:37:04,389
Eight thousand?

356
00:37:05,807 --> 00:37:07,934
You counting every dollar of that as two?

357
00:37:10,603 --> 00:37:12,355
That's what he said he owed.

358
00:37:13,523 --> 00:37:16,443
Eight thousand was the principal.
What about the rest?

359
00:37:16,985 --> 00:37:19,070
He's missed four payments.

360
00:37:20,238 --> 00:37:23,408
He owed us 13,500 and change.

361
00:37:23,491 --> 00:37:24,743
I'm doing you a favor.

362
00:37:24,826 --> 00:37:26,202
Why don't you go rob a bank?

363
00:37:30,081 --> 00:37:32,292
Who do you think you are,
talking to me like that?

364
00:37:32,375 --> 00:37:33,752
You're awful fond of talking.

365
00:37:33,835 --> 00:37:36,713
Ah-Kwong, take him in there
and have a nice long chat with him.

366
00:37:36,796 --> 00:37:39,048
- We'll talk about your mother!
- Shut up!

367
00:37:39,632 --> 00:37:41,092
Get out of here!

368
00:37:42,886 --> 00:37:43,786
Get out!

369
00:37:55,398 --> 00:37:58,193
Your brother's lucky
he's working under you.

370
00:37:59,027 --> 00:38:00,945
Anyone else and he'd be dead by now.

371
00:38:02,155 --> 00:38:03,656
Let's cut the small talk.

372
00:38:04,574 --> 00:38:06,326
Enough beating around the bush.

373
00:38:08,828 --> 00:38:10,163
Well?

374
00:38:10,246 --> 00:38:11,831
First, I've paid off the principal,

375
00:38:11,915 --> 00:38:14,501
but he really doesn't have the interest.

376
00:38:14,584 --> 00:38:16,544
We'll have to postpone two more payments.

377
00:38:16,628 --> 00:38:19,631
Two more? Why not just wait till I'm dead
and burn it as an offering?

378
00:38:21,633 --> 00:38:24,594
If you don't trust him, trust me.
I'm good for it.

379
00:38:26,221 --> 00:38:27,889
But I don't have the money now.

380
00:38:27,972 --> 00:38:29,808
I'll give it to you in a couple days.

381
00:38:32,352 --> 00:38:35,647
How can you be a big brother
if you don't even have that much?

382
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:37,649
Better go be a farmer or something.

383
00:38:37,732 --> 00:38:41,110
I thought you had money,
so I agreed to talk to you.

384
00:38:41,945 --> 00:38:44,572
You're a sorry excuse for a big brother.

385
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:53,998
You really want it now?

386
00:38:55,834 --> 00:38:59,212
- What? You're crazy.
- What?

387
00:38:59,629 --> 00:39:01,506
Sure, I'll take it if you have it now.

388
00:39:05,051 --> 00:39:06,845
Okay. Let me make a call first.

389
00:39:17,355 --> 00:39:19,399
Why are you just sitting there?

390
00:39:19,482 --> 00:39:21,818
Your boss told you to talk with me,
so talk!

391
00:39:21,901 --> 00:39:23,963
What's your father's name?
What's your mother called?

392
00:39:23,987 --> 00:39:25,738
Stop joking around, Fly.

393
00:39:25,822 --> 00:39:28,491
Why don't you talk to me?
Don't you have any parents?

394
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:36,291
Are you the boss?

395
00:39:39,919 --> 00:39:41,004
Stay back!

396
00:39:42,005 --> 00:39:46,134
I have a little problem.
Could you lend me some money?

397
00:39:46,217 --> 00:39:47,510
Yes, I could.

398
00:39:47,594 --> 00:39:48,928
Fly.

399
00:39:51,598 --> 00:39:53,933
I'm borrowing the money from your boss.

400
00:39:54,017 --> 00:39:55,852
You can take it or leave it,

401
00:39:55,935 --> 00:39:58,438
but there's no debt between us
from now on.

402
00:39:58,521 --> 00:40:02,483
If I get rich someday,
I'll pay you back.

403
00:40:02,567 --> 00:40:05,862
You were wrong to help this guy
rip us off at high interest! Right?

404
00:40:05,945 --> 00:40:06,946
Right!

405
00:40:07,030 --> 00:40:09,115
What are you waiting for?
Give Tony the money.

406
00:40:09,198 --> 00:40:10,700
We're even now.

407
00:40:13,620 --> 00:40:16,664
And here's a little extra,
my gift to you.

408
00:40:22,086 --> 00:40:24,839
Think you're tough, huh?
Shafting me in my own place!

409
00:40:27,717 --> 00:40:29,677
You're something yourself,
taking us for fools.

410
00:40:30,386 --> 00:40:31,888
Come here a minute.

411
00:40:32,847 --> 00:40:34,182
Let's go.

412
00:40:43,274 --> 00:40:46,694
Tony, I pay you to guard this place,

413
00:40:46,778 --> 00:40:49,530
not to bring in hoodlums to rob me!

414
00:40:49,614 --> 00:40:51,366
What's the meaning of this?

415
00:40:51,449 --> 00:40:53,952
Boss, he just lost his temper.

416
00:41:10,426 --> 00:41:12,303
Things are heating up on the street,

417
00:41:12,387 --> 00:41:14,472
and you two are still at each other!

418
00:41:14,555 --> 00:41:16,432
Don't you have any respect for me?

419
00:41:17,308 --> 00:41:19,018
He started it.

420
00:41:20,645 --> 00:41:22,021
First he refuses to pay his debt,

421
00:41:22,105 --> 00:41:24,524
then he causes trouble in my place
and robs my boss.

422
00:41:25,274 --> 00:41:28,152
He's been wrong all the way
down the line, Godfather.

423
00:41:28,778 --> 00:41:31,739
You knew he was crazy.
You shouldn't have bugged him!

424
00:41:32,824 --> 00:41:35,952
And you've gone too far,
taking advantage of him.

425
00:41:37,704 --> 00:41:39,956
You knew that was his turf.

426
00:41:40,999 --> 00:41:44,085
Godfather, I was just trying
to pay him back.

427
00:41:44,585 --> 00:41:48,673
He wanted the money back, so I gave it.
It was a fair exchange.

428
00:41:48,756 --> 00:41:51,843
- Fair?
- What are you doing?

429
00:41:51,926 --> 00:41:54,554
I'm still the one
who makes the decisions around here!

430
00:41:54,637 --> 00:42:00,727
Damn it! Just make your payment every month,
and that settles that!

431
00:42:00,810 --> 00:42:02,270
Now shake on it!

432
00:42:05,648 --> 00:42:08,693
Well? I told you to shake on it.

433
00:42:08,776 --> 00:42:10,111
Do it!

434
00:42:11,112 --> 00:42:12,113
Shake!

435
00:42:17,827 --> 00:42:20,329
That traitor Ah-Kay is a snitch.

436
00:42:21,247 --> 00:42:22,874
We can't let him live.

437
00:42:23,750 --> 00:42:26,085
You gotta kill him
before he goes to court.

438
00:42:26,169 --> 00:42:27,420
What do you say?

439
00:42:28,504 --> 00:42:31,382
It's a tough job.
Who should we send?

440
00:42:31,966 --> 00:42:35,720
I don't want an outsider handling this.
Here's what we'll do.

441
00:42:35,803 --> 00:42:40,892
You two find some smart boys
to draw lots day after tomorrow.

442
00:42:42,810 --> 00:42:47,315
This guy's perfect.
He acts all tough and brave.

443
00:42:47,398 --> 00:42:49,984
Send your younger brother,
if he wants to do it.

444
00:42:50,068 --> 00:42:51,444
I'll cancel his debt,

445
00:42:51,527 --> 00:42:54,489
and we'll look after his family,
if he dies.

446
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:55,740
You got the guts?

447
00:42:55,823 --> 00:42:58,034
What? You trying to scare me?

448
00:42:58,618 --> 00:43:00,036
Shut up.

449
00:43:01,537 --> 00:43:05,541
Don't pick on the little guys.
You and me are the best here.

450
00:43:06,042 --> 00:43:08,336
It's either you or me.

451
00:43:08,419 --> 00:43:10,463
I'll do it if you won't.

452
00:43:10,546 --> 00:43:12,298
Just say the word and I'll take it.

453
00:43:14,467 --> 00:43:17,678
You'll have to do it,
if you don't speak up.

454
00:43:18,221 --> 00:43:20,431
Say you don't want to
and admit you're a coward.

455
00:43:20,515 --> 00:43:22,308
Then I'll take it on!

456
00:43:22,934 --> 00:43:24,352
Stop dreaming!

457
00:43:24,435 --> 00:43:27,271
You two ganging up on me?

458
00:43:27,355 --> 00:43:30,024
Fine! I'll kill you two first!

459
00:43:30,108 --> 00:43:32,026
Not again! Stop arguing!

460
00:43:32,652 --> 00:43:35,988
I have my own idea how to handle this.
Now get out of here, all of you.

461
00:43:36,614 --> 00:43:38,366
Good-bye, Godfather.

462
00:43:40,576 --> 00:43:42,161
<i>Ah-Wah, come back here.</i>

463
00:43:44,539 --> 00:43:45,540
What is it?

464
00:43:45,623 --> 00:43:49,043
I know you and your brother
are good friends.

465
00:43:49,127 --> 00:43:50,878
But he's too crazy.

466
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:54,757
Straighten him out.
He's like a time bomb.

467
00:43:54,841 --> 00:43:56,843
One of these days he'll get you killed.

468
00:43:56,926 --> 00:43:58,261
I know.

469
00:43:59,262 --> 00:44:00,638
I've thought about that.

470
00:44:00,721 --> 00:44:02,849
I want to find him a normal job.

471
00:44:02,932 --> 00:44:04,142
Good idea.

472
00:44:04,267 --> 00:44:07,395
Fish balls!

473
00:44:10,940 --> 00:44:12,775
That's it for today. Time to go home!

474
00:44:13,901 --> 00:44:15,486
Brother Wah is here.

475
00:44:19,615 --> 00:44:21,450
Help me out here.

476
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:31,043
Fish balls!
Get your fish balls!

477
00:44:33,254 --> 00:44:35,840
- Hey, Big Brother.
- Give me one. How's it going?

478
00:44:37,175 --> 00:44:38,384
How do you think?

479
00:44:38,467 --> 00:44:40,928
Think I can't handle a food cart?

480
00:44:42,054 --> 00:44:43,723
You know who you're talking to.

481
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:50,479
Take it slow.
You'll move up into the big time.

482
00:44:50,563 --> 00:44:53,399
Right. Fish balls here today,

483
00:44:54,233 --> 00:44:56,360
bombs in the Middle East tomorrow.

484
00:44:56,444 --> 00:44:58,654
- You jerk!
- Police!

485
00:45:01,032 --> 00:45:02,700
Stop!

486
00:45:03,993 --> 00:45:05,203
The police are coming!

487
00:45:05,286 --> 00:45:07,038
Who gives a shit?

488
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:09,415
Hey, fish ball man! Is this your cart?

489
00:45:09,498 --> 00:45:11,209
- What did you call me?
- Fish ball man.

490
00:45:11,292 --> 00:45:12,501
What?

491
00:45:12,585 --> 00:45:15,254
If you don't sell fish balls,
what's with those scissors?

492
00:45:15,713 --> 00:45:18,341
Scissors mean I sell fish balls?
Are you crazy?

493
00:45:18,424 --> 00:45:19,967
I'm just trimming my nose hairs.

494
00:45:20,968 --> 00:45:25,181
- So it's not your cart. Take it away!
- Fine! Take it!

495
00:45:25,264 --> 00:45:28,684
Hey, what are you doing?
That cart cost money!

496
00:45:28,768 --> 00:45:30,978
Saving face is what matters, not money.

497
00:45:31,062 --> 00:45:33,564
I may not be famous,
but people here know me.

498
00:45:33,648 --> 00:45:35,524
I don't want to sell fish balls!

499
00:45:35,608 --> 00:45:36,901
I have to live around here!

500
00:45:39,195 --> 00:45:42,448
Out of my way!
You don't own the sidewalk!

501
00:45:43,866 --> 00:45:46,285
It's just a job! No need to be ashamed!

502
00:45:46,369 --> 00:45:47,995
I don't like selling fish balls!

503
00:45:48,079 --> 00:45:50,122
Then what do you want to sell?

504
00:45:50,206 --> 00:45:52,833
You can't just hang around
doing nothing.

505
00:45:52,917 --> 00:45:54,460
You're not cut out for the gang!

506
00:45:54,543 --> 00:45:57,922
Yeah, I know!
I'm Mr. Fish Balls!

507
00:45:59,215 --> 00:46:01,050
Fine! I'll do it 'cause you say so,

508
00:46:01,801 --> 00:46:04,929
but when I can't stand it anymore,
